HEADWORD: Tanystomata
<hw>Tan`y*stom"a*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ to stretch + <?/, <?/, mouth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of dipterous insects in which the proboscis is large and
contains lancelike mandibles and maxillae. The horseflies and robber
flies are examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

